'''M. V. Pylee''' ( 5 October 1919 - 30 December 2017) was an Indian scholar, educationist and management guru, considered by many as the father of management education in Kerala<ref>[http://www.dcsmat.ac.in/governing-council DCSMAT Governing Council<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530064610/http://www.dcsmat.ac.in/governing-council |date=30 May 2014 }}</ref> and an authority on Constitutional Law. He was awarded [[Padmabhushan]] in 2006 by Government of India for his contributions to the fields of education and management.<ref>[[Padma Bhushan Awards (2000–2009)|Padma Bhushan Awards (2000–09) – Wikipedia, the free encyclopaedia]]</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=M.V. Pylee passes away |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/mv-pylee-passes-away/article22334858.ece |publisher=The Hindu |accessdate=11 August 2018}}</ref>

==Biography==
Moolamattom Varkey Pylee was born in [[Pulinkunnoo]] on 5 October 1919.<ref name="Autograph of M. V. Pylee">{{cite web | url=http://www.indianautographs.com/productdetail-125440.html | title=Autograph of M. V. Pylee | publisher=Indian Autographs | date=2016 | accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref> He had extensive education starting at Pulinkunnoo St. Joseph's Higher Secondary School and held degrees such as M. A. (Luck). D. Litt. (Pat) and LL. M. ([[Harvard University|Harvard]]). He was also honoured with D. Litt. from [[Banares Hindu University]].

His wife, Elsie Pylee, died in 2004.<ref>[http://www.hindu.com/2004/06/12/stories/2004061214390300.htm The Hindu : Kerala / Kochi News : Around the City<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The couple had three children, two daughters and one son. Prof. Pylee resided in [[Kalamassery]], in Ernakulam.

An award has been instituted by [[Cochin University of Science and Technology]], '''M. V. Pylee Award''', given once in three years, carrying a cash prize of Rs 200,000, a memento and citation for excellence in teaching and research and contribution to academic community.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/varanasi/Banaras-Hindu-University-VC-wins-MV-Pylee-award-for-best-academician/articleshow/16678631.cms Banaras Hindu University VC wins MV Pylee award for best academician – The Times of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

Cochin University of Science and Technology, St. Berchman's College, Changanacherry, St. Joseph's School Pulimkunnu, St. Agnus College, Mangalore, Kerala Higher Education Trust, Good Samaritan project, India and others have benefitted from the Trust endowments.<ref>[http://mvpylee.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=102&Itemid=53 Profile<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

==Works==
M. V. Pylee authored several books in English and Malayalam.<ref>[http://mvpylee.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=94&Itemid=27 Selected Works]</ref><ref>[https://www.google.ae/search?tbo=p&tbm=bks&q=inauthor:%22Moolamattom+Varkey+Pylee%22 Works of Moolamattom Varkey Pylee at Google Books]</ref>

