==Awards==
{{more citations needed|section|date=March 2017}}
* [[Padmabhushan]] Award by Government of India, 2006.
* Paramacharya Award of the Centurion Trust, Chennai, 2003.
* Shyamlal Gupta Award −2001 for Life Time Contribution to Education.
* Life Time Achievement Award in appreciation of services to Management Education by SMSA Association, Cochin University – 2000.
* International Award for Distinguished Service to Global Higher Education, IFACHE, Bethlahem, Israel, 2000.
* Man of the Year Award, [[Cambridge University]], England, 1998.
* National Super Brain Award, [[Competition Success Review]], New Delhi, 1998.
* Akshardham Award, Gandhi Nagar, Gujarat, for "Unique achievements in the field of Management".
* Nedumkunnam Award by the Kerala History Congress, 1991 for the best History Book in Malayalam.
* Distinguished Author Award at the Golden Jubilee Celebration of S. Chand and Company, Publishers, New Delhi, 1989.
* Distinguished Leadership Award for Outstanding Service to teaching and Management Profession (1990).
* Management Leadership Award at the All India Seminar on Professional Management held at Calicut, Kerala – 1990.
* Honorary Membership, Kerala Management Association – 1985.
* Honorary Membership, Kerala State Productivity Council – 1985.
* Management Leadership Award – KMA – 1986.
* Vangala Narasimagaru Memorial Gold Medal (1984) for securing First class First in M.A. Degree Examination, [[Lucknow University]]. 
* [[Emeritus Professor]]ship – [[University of Cochin]] – 1986.
* Fulbright Smith-mundt Scholar at [[Harvard University]] (1953–54<ref name=autogenerated1 />).

